WEBVTT



00:00:23.744 --> 00:00:27.488
Growing spiritually means growing in your trust and obedience of Him.

00:00:27.424 --> 00:00:31.904
But what does an intimate relationship with God look like? What does that even mean?

00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:39.392
Tonight Joel Thomas is going to spend a few minutes talking about that. But before he does, we went around our neighborhood getting some thoughts on the subject.

00:00:49.856 --> 00:00:51.072
Heavenly Father.

00:00:51.648 --> 00:00:58.528
Someone to take care of you and watch over you. Do you feel just a spiritual well-being when you hear the words?

00:00:58.592 --> 00:00:59.616
God.

00:00:59.872 --> 00:01:01.696
There's only one.

00:01:05.856 --> 00:01:07.488
Very nice

00:01:07.872 --> 00:01:09.728
Never made it all.

00:01:10.016 --> 00:01:12.736
I don't see him with having much personality.

00:01:12.576 --> 00:01:16.352
Leaving the personality to his angels and saints.

00:01:16.544 --> 00:01:19.936
No, I don't think there's any personal. I think it's very...

00:01:19.936 --> 00:01:22.240
Like, if anything, I think it's just...

00:01:22.368 --> 00:01:24.864
I don't envision a person...

00:01:24.768 --> 00:01:26.400
By any means whatsoever.

00:01:26.496 --> 00:01:34.240
This person is probably the most interesting personality of all. So just because all of the variations of it,

00:01:34.048 --> 00:01:37.600
End up being reflected in what type of people are.

00:01:37.568 --> 00:01:39.072
Here on this

00:01:39.040 --> 00:01:44.704
Earther in this universe so somebody that's like all-knowing and can

00:01:44.544 --> 00:01:49.696
You know, know your steps before you take them and also like lead you down the right path.

00:01:53.728 --> 00:01:55.968
It depends on what

00:01:55.936 --> 00:01:58.144
How people interpret

00:01:58.048 --> 00:01:59.616
Um, how, how,

00:01:59.776 --> 00:02:04.832
He or she communicates to you. I mean, you know, because it could be for me. It's, you know, it's...

00:02:04.512 --> 00:02:08.768
intuition and I just said voice that just says to you

00:02:08.544 --> 00:02:09.920
Um...

00:02:09.696 --> 00:02:16.064
In certain direction, on certain questions. I think it's possible to feel a godlike presence.

00:02:15.904 --> 00:02:20.704
Do I believe you can have a conversation and expect an actual reply? No, I do not.

00:02:20.576 --> 00:02:29.792
I feel like for me it's like a continual conversation kind of throughout the day, whatever I'm kind of struggling with or need help with, and I constantly, um,

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:35.680
I have to remind myself that he's kind of always with me because sometimes I start stressing out about...

00:02:35.424 --> 00:02:37.824
you know, whatever, and I forget to just...

00:02:37.792 --> 00:02:39.232
Just call on him.

00:02:44.384 --> 00:02:46.336
People believe in a higher power

00:02:46.048 --> 00:02:49.344
It allows them to wield a lot of power.

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:52.128
And so they can leverage that.

00:02:52.032 --> 00:02:53.440
power against.

00:02:54.048 --> 00:02:58.912
So I actually think religion is actually the cause of the majority of problems in the world.

00:02:58.976 --> 00:03:04.320
I mean, I think that everyone has kind of their own relationship and communicates in their own different way, whether it's

00:03:04.608 --> 00:03:07.936
Just being thankful or praying or

00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:11.904
You know, meditation, whatever that is, but that connection.

00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:16.704
I do. I think you can have a very spiritual relationship with whatever God

00:03:16.832 --> 00:03:22.880
You believe in. I think it's important that if you're going to be spiritual, you sort of seek that.

00:03:23.136 --> 00:03:25.408
You're never really finished with it though.

00:03:25.600 --> 00:03:28.768
Yeah, I think that God would be such.

00:03:28.992 --> 00:03:34.560
Such a higher being that it's not possible really to ever know and fully understand it.

00:03:55.136 --> 00:04:05.184
I recently had the opportunity to reconnect with an old friend from childhood over coffee, and it was amazing. After just a few moments and a few sentences, it was like no time had passed at all. It was so easy. I mean, 10 years.

00:04:04.704 --> 00:04:14.752
10 years had passed and yet this friend that had been like one of my closest friends growing up again felt like one of my closest friends. Some of you may have experienced the same thing. You may have a friend or

00:04:14.272 --> 00:04:17.952
Or a few friends that that happens with. But isn't that rare?

00:04:18.016 --> 00:04:21.184
Why is it that that happens that way? Is it chemistry?

00:04:20.864 --> 00:04:22.528
It's a personality.

00:04:22.304 --> 00:04:23.776
Is it history?

00:04:24.032 --> 00:04:26.080
I believe it's by design.

00:04:25.952 --> 00:04:36.000
I believe that we find in the scriptures and the genesis account of creation the answer to what this actually is. In fact, it says this, it says, "Let us make man in our

00:04:35.520 --> 00:04:37.216
And in our image, God is

00:04:37.024 --> 00:04:45.088
in our likeness. Now that's amazing. God decided of all the things He created in the world, He decided to create you.

00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:45.888
And me.

00:04:45.632 --> 00:04:53.184
in his likeness. Now, it may seem a little strange, but God also says, if you notice how he says it, he says, "Let us know."

00:04:52.992 --> 00:05:00.864
make mankind in our image, in our likeness. We find out throughout the scriptures that there really is only one God, we're told.

00:05:00.704 --> 00:05:10.496
But that God is in three persons: God the Father, and God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit, which is commonly known as the Trinity. God in three persons, yet one.

00:05:10.688 --> 00:05:12.576
And he created you.

00:05:12.352 --> 00:05:22.400
And he created me with that same capacity, with that same nature, the capacity for oneness of relationship. In fact, in the very first human relationship, we see a model for

00:05:21.920 --> 00:05:28.576
model for this as Adam and Eve are instructed to join together and become one flesh.

00:05:29.088 --> 00:05:39.136
And the type of close one relationship that we experience that's modeled in marriage is the type of relationship that God created us with the possibility for.

00:05:38.656 --> 00:05:48.704
In fact, in the Gospel of John, John records a prayer of Jesus where he's praying to the Father and he prays that we would be one. He prays for all believers together that we would be one.

00:05:48.224 --> 00:05:58.272
He prays to the Father. He says, Father, as I am in you and as you are in me, may they also be in us and may we all be one together.

00:05:57.792 --> 00:06:07.840
together. He prayed that you and I would have the ability to be one with one another. Now, the amazing thing about that language is this is language of access. Jesus made it possible.

00:06:07.360 --> 00:06:17.408
it possible for you and I to have access to the Father. And Jesus prayed that this is what would be possible for us. My guess is that the people that you're closest with in life,

00:06:16.928 --> 00:06:19.904
They have special access to you.

00:06:19.808 --> 00:06:22.528
To your thoughts and to your emotions.

00:06:22.272 --> 00:06:23.936
To the things you do.

00:06:23.904 --> 00:06:28.128
And when you give others access, relationships deepen.

00:06:27.904 --> 00:06:33.568
The greater the access, the greater the intimacy in our relationship with each other,

00:06:33.248 --> 00:06:36.064
And in our relationship with god.

00:06:36.032 --> 00:06:41.344
I believe that's why in another one of John's writings in the book of Revelation, we see Jesus saying,

00:06:41.216 --> 00:06:43.648
I stand at the door and I knock.

00:06:43.584 --> 00:06:52.512
And if you'll open the door, I'll come in and I'll eat with you and you with me. This is figurative language for community, for relationship, for communion.

00:06:52.352 --> 00:06:53.760
For intimacy.

00:06:53.600 --> 00:07:03.648
When we open the door to our Heavenly Father, when we open the door to our relationships, we open the door to our career, we open the door to our finances, we open the door to our thought life. As we open the door to our

00:07:03.168 --> 00:07:13.216
Lord, every area of our lives, allowing God to speak into our lives through his word and through others, our relationship with him deepens. Our intimacy with God grows and what needs to be done.

00:07:12.736 --> 00:07:18.976
And what Jesus prayed actually becomes possible for you and for me.

00:07:31.072 --> 00:07:33.344
But giving God full access to your life.

00:07:33.088 --> 00:07:41.664
Being open and honest about what's really going on in your heart is essential to growing spiritually and to forming healthy relationships. And that's what you're going to talk about tonight.

00:07:41.696 --> 00:07:49.088
But before you do, I want to remind you that for people to be authentic about what's really going on in their lives and to share that with the group,

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:52.864
They have to know that what's being said in group stays in group.

00:07:52.768 --> 00:07:56.192
So keep that in mind tonight and in the discussions to come.
